This probably goes without saying, but you will not find quality Jamaican food at this 'restaurant'. There are far too many authentic Jamaican food restaurants in the DMV area to choose from to consider this place.  The patties that I ordered were dry and nearly devoid of contents. The Jerk Chicken sandwich I ordered tasted like frozen rotisserie chicken strips sprinkled with a small amount of jerk chicken BBQ that one can find in a normal grocery store. The bun and cheese barely had any cheese on it. All of this was ridiculously priced for no reason, because it is clear that they aren't importing ingredients.  Other than that, the staff was nice enough and the location is quite convenient. However, I arrived just 10 minutes before the five guys opened and decided I couldn't wait. If I could go back, I'd wait an hour for Five Guys before ever considering this place again.
